The paper proposes a framework to address scalability and out-of-sample problems in subspace clustering algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves clustering and coding strategies, which are related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
